Ingredients
* 4 skinless, boneless chicken breast halves
* salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste
* 2 eggs
* 1 cup italian seasoned bread crumbs, or more as needed
* 2 tablespoons all-purpose flour, or more if needed
* 1 oil or butter for frying
* 1 can or small bottle prepared tomato sauce
* 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese
* 1/4 cup shredded mozzarella
* 1/2 cup grated or shredded provolone cheese (optional)
* 1/4 cup chopped fresh basil
* 1 tablespoon olive oil

Directions
* Preheat an oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C).
* Beat eggs in a shallow bowl
* Place bread crumbs in a shallow dish
* Place flour in a shallow dish
* Place chicken breasts between two sheets of plastic (plastic wrap, resealable freezer bags) on a cutting board. Firmly pound chicken with the smooth side of a meat mallet to a thickness of 1/2-inch.
* Season chicken thoroughly with salt and pepper.
* Flour chicken on both sides
* Dip flour coated chicken breast in beaten eggs.
* Dip chicken breasts in breadcrumb mixture, pressing the crumbs into both sides.
* Repeat for each breast.
* Heat oil (or butter) in a large skillet on medium-high heat until it begins to shimmer.
* Cook chicken until golden, about 2 minutes on each side. The chicken will finish cooking in the oven.
* Place chicken in bottom of a baking dish
* Top chicken with can of tomato sauce.
* Place layer of shredded cheeses, fresh basil. Drizzle with olive oil.
* Bake in the preheated oven until cheese is browned and bubbly, and chicken breasts are no longer pink in the center, 15 to 20 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).

Notes
* Taken From https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/223042/chicken-parmesan/
